Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a large #pot of salted water.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press).

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g}(chopped) (stalks and all).

Zest and quarter the @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Lay the @salmon{200%g} onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, then season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Sprinkle over the lemon zest.

When the oven is hot, roast the salmon on the top shelf until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish. Salmon is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the oven and set aside.

Meanwhile, add the @linguine{180%g} to the boiling water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander and pop back in the pot, off the heat.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.

Meanwhile, place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @peas{120%g} and garlic. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @vegetable stock{1%sachet} along with 100ml @water{to taste} (per 2P). Simmer until slightly reduced, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{110%g}, peas, @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} (use less if you don't like spice), half the parsley and lemon juice to taste.

Simmer until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Loosen the sauce with a splash of @water{to taste} if you feel it's too thick.

Once the salmon is cooked, mix the salmon into the creamy sauce.

Add the cooked pasta and toss to coat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide your creamy salmon linguine between bowls.

Top with a scattering of the remaining parsley.

Serve any remaining lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over.